gomodel:SYNGO_1828  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig. 3d,e,f ; siRNA-mediated knockdown of IL-1RAcP isoforms in cortical neurons reduced the staining signals for presynaptic Bassoon and decreased the number of dendritic spines.\nLiteral:\n\"The siRNA against Il1rap was transfected into cultured cortical neurons at DIV 10. After 4d of incubation, we observed a significant reduction of staining signals\nfor presynaptic Bassoon along the dendrites of the transfected cortical neurons and a decrease of number of dendritic protrusions (Fig. 3D-F)\"\n\nFig. 4a,b; transfected FLAG-IL-1RAcP in cortical neurons increased punctate immunostaining signals for Bassoon\nLiteral:\n\"Transfection of cultured cortical neurons at DIV 12 with the expression vector for FLAG-IL-1RAcP increased punctate immunostaining signals for Bassoon but exerted little effect on dendritic protrusions (Fig. 4)\n\nFig.8 IL-1RAcPb and IL-1RAcP (not shown) requires PTPδ for presynaptic differentiation. Experimental description: Fig. 1; Fig. 3d,e; Fig. 4a,b. Mouse IL-1RAcP is overexpressed HEK293T cells co-cultured with mouse cortical neurons and transfecetd in mouse cortical neurons\nLiteral from M&M\n- Overexpressed 1RAcP is of mouse species: \"The entire coding sequences of mouse IL-1RAcP, IL-1RAcPb, ...\"\n\"Cell cultures, transfection, and coculture assay. Primary cortical cultures were prepared from mice at postnatal day 0 (P0) essentially as described previously\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2949-9725" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0662-9523" ;
        dc:date           "2018-05-29" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_1828" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

